OL,4,CBuilders told to remove 'unfair' ground
OL,5,Crent terms
OL,6, Housebuilders Countryside and Taylor
OL,7, Wimpey have been told to change their
OL,8, leasehold contract terms by the UK
OL,9, competition watchdog or face legal
OL,10, action.
OL,12,FThe Competition and Markets Authority
OL,13,F(CMA) said the "unfair" terms, which
OL,14,Fdouble ground every 10 to 15 years,
OL,15,F"trap" people.
OL,17,FIt said the contract means people can
OL,18,Fstruggle to sell or mortgage homes.
OL,20,FThe builders said they had already
OL,21,Ftaken steps that address the issue.
